data.enText: a large amount of a substance that does not have a definite shape or form

data.chText: 从山上滚下来的一堆积雪和石块
data.enText: a mass of snow and rocks falling down the mountain

data.chText: 远远地看去，那座山是黑魆魆一片。
data.enText: The hill appeared as a black mass in the distance.
The sky was full of dark masses of clouds.
a large amount or quantity of sth
a mass of blonde hair

data.chText: 我开始认真筛选大量的证据。
data.enText: I began sifting through the mass of evidence.
a large number of people or things grouped together, often in a confused way

data.chText: 我在人群里挤来挤去，挤到了出口处。
data.enText: I struggled through the mass of people to the exit.

data.chText: 纸上写满了密密麻麻的数字。
data.enText: The page was covered with a mass of figures.
a large number or amount of sth
There were masses of people in the shops yesterday.

data.chText: 我有一大堆的工作要做。
data.enText: I've got masses of work to do.

data.chText: 别再给我了，我已经吃了很多了！
data.enText: Don't give me any more. I've eaten masses!
the ordinary people in society who are not leaders or who are considered to be not very well educated

data.chText: 政府试图压制群众不满情绪的做法
data.enText: government attempts to suppress dissatisfaction among the masses

data.chText: 普及科学知识的电视节目
data.enText: a TV programme that brings science to the masses
the most; the majority

data.chText: 大多数教师和家长并不赞成这些改革。
data.enText: The reforms are unpopular with the mass of teachers and parents.
the quantity of material that sth contains
calculating the mass of a planet

data.text: Weight is used in non-technical language for this meaning.
非专业语言用weight表示此义。

data.chText: 大批的；数量极多的；广泛的

weapons of mass destruction

data.chText: 他们的最新产品瞄准了大众市场。
data.enText: Their latest product is aimed at the mass market .
to come together in large numbers; to gather people or things together in large numbers

Dark clouds massed on the horizon.

data.chText: 将军把军队都集中起来准备发动最后的进攻。
data.enText: The general massed his troops for a final attack.
the massed ranks of his political opponents

tr: the property of a body that causes it to have weight in a gravitational field
the property of something that is great in magnitude
example: it is cheaper to buy it in bulk
he received a mass of correspondence

tr: an ill-structured collection of similar things (objects or people)

example: separate the warriors from the mass

tr: a body of matter without definite shape
(often followed by `of') a large number or amount or extent
example: he made a mint on the stock market
see the rest of the winners in our huge passel of photos

tr: join together into a mass or collect or form a mass
example: Crowds were massing outside the palace

tr: formed of separate units gathered into a mass or whole
example: aggregate expenses include expenses of all divisions combined for the entire year

value.def: A mass of things is a large number of them grouped together.

example.ex: On his desk is a mass of books and papers.
example.tran: 他的书桌上有大堆的书籍和文件。

value.def: A mass of something is a large amount of it.

example.ex: She had a mass of auburn hair.
example.tran: 她有一头浓密的棕发。

value.def: Masses of something means a great deal of it.

example.ex: There's masses of work for her to do...
example.tran: 她有一大堆的工作要做。

example.ex: It has masses of flowers each year.
example.tran: 它每年都开许多花。

value.def: Mass is used to describe something which involves or affects a very large number of people.

example.ex: ...ideas on combating mass unemployment...
example.tran: 对付大量失业的点子

example.ex: All the lights went off, and mass hysteria broke out.
example.tran: 所有的灯都熄灭了，大家都变得歇斯底里起来。

example.ex: ...weapons of mass destruction.
example.tran: 大规模杀伤性武器

example.ex: ...the harm caused by mass tourism.
example.tran: 大众旅游造成的危害

value.def: A mass of a solid substance, a liquid, or a gas is an amount of it, especially a large amount which has no definite shape.

example.ex: ...before it cools and sets into a solid mass...
example.tran: 在它冷却成为固态之前

example.ex: The fourteenth century cathedral was reduced to a mass of rubble.
example.tran: 这座14世纪的大教堂变成了一堆瓦砾。

example.ex: ...the strong temperature difference between the two masses of air.
example.tran: 两个气团之间强烈的温差

value.def: If you talk about the masses, you mean the ordinary people in society, in contrast to the leaders or the highly educated people.

example.ex: His music is commercial. It is aimed at the masses...
example.tran: 他的音乐走商业化路线，针对的是一般大众。

example.ex: This issue has aroused much resentment among the masses.
example.tran: 这个问题在民众中间引起了强烈的不满。

example.ex: ...appealing to the middle class and business as well as the masses.
example.tran: 符合中产阶级、商务人士和普通百姓的需要

value.tran: （与领导或受过高等教育的人相对的）普通老百姓，民众，平民大众

value.def: The mass of people are most of the people in a country, society, or group.

example.ex: The 1939-45 world war involved the mass of the population...
example.tran: 1939至1945年间的世界大战使大多数民众卷入其中。

example.ex: Schools allowed the mass of children to leave school at 16 with poor qualifications.
example.tran: 学校允许大部分考试成绩差的学生16岁时毕业离校。

value.def: A mass of people is a large crowd of them.

example.ex: ...masses of excited people clogged the streets.
example.tran: 情绪激动的人群挤满了街道。

example.ex: ...a mass of grinning teenage faces.
example.tran: 一张张少年的笑脸

value.def: When people or things mass, or when you mass them, they gather together into a large crowd or group.

example.ex: Shortly after the workers went on strike, police began to mass at the shipyard...
example.tran: 工人们罢工后不久，警察就开始在船厂集结。

example.ex: The clouds massed, whipped up by the wind...
example.tran: 云卷云舒随风起。

example.ex: The General was massing his troops for a counterattack.
example.tran: 将军正在集结部队准备反攻。

value.def: If you say that something is a mass of things, you mean that it is covered with them or full of them.

example.ex: His body was a mass of sores...
example.tran: 他遍体鳞伤。

example.ex: In the spring, the meadow is a mass of daffodils.
example.tran: 春天，草地上开满了黄水仙。

value.def: In physics, the mass of an object is the amount of physical matter that it has.

example.ex: Astronomers know that Pluto and Triton have nearly the same size, mass, and density.
example.tran: 天文学家知道冥王星与海卫一拥有几乎相同的体积、质量与密度。

value.def: Mass is a Christian church ceremony, especially in a Roman Catholic or Orthodox church, during which people eat bread and drink wine in order to remember the last meal of Jesus Christ.

example.ex: She attended a convent school and went to Mass each day.
example.tran: 她上的是教会学校，每天都去做弥撒。

value.tran: 弥撒(尤指天主教或东正教的圣餐仪式，以此纪念耶稣基督的最后的晚餐)

value.def: A Mass is a piece of music which uses the prayers from the Christian ceremony of Mass as the words that are sung.
